    dc:creator "Smales, Lesley" ;
    dc:date "2019" ;
    dc:title "Gastrointestinal nematodes of Paramelomys platyops (Rodentia: Muridae) from Papua Indonesia and Papua New Guinea with the descriptions of a new genus and five new species of Heligmonellidae (Nematoda: Trichostrongylina) and a key to the species of Hughjonestrongylus" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3468113> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3468113>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–15. Flannerystrongylus abulus n. gen., n. sp. In all illustrations of the synlophe in transverse section the dorsal aspect of the body is oriented towards the top of the page and the left side of the nematode to the left of the page. The dorsal and ventral (numbers with superscripts) ridges are numbered. 1. Male, anterior end, lateral view; 2. Female, transverse section, anterior body; 3. Male, cephalic vesicle, lateral view; 4. Female posterior end showing torsion; 5. Female, transverse section, mid body; 6. Male, transverse section, mid body; 7. Female posterior end, ventral view showing ovejector; 8. Female, transverse section posterior body; 9. Spicule, proximal end; 10. Male, transverse section posterior body; 11. Gubernaculum and spicule tips, lateral view; 12. Bursa, left lateral view, bursal rays numbered 13. Genital cone, lateral view; 14. Dorsal ray 15. Bursa, right lateral view. Scale bars in µm: 1, 4, 7, 12, 15, 100; 2, 3, 5, 6, 8–10, 13, 25." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3468113/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

